{"kind":"article","topicSections":[{"anchor":"Topics","identifiers":["doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/flatMap(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/flatMapAndMergeError(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/map(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/mapAndMergeError(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/mapFailureToSuccess(_:)","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/mapFailureToSuccessAndErrorToFailure(_:)"]}],"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"level":5,"text":"General transformation","type":"heading","anchor":"General-transformation"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Transforming a value, by applying a function to it using dot syntax, is sometimes an easier-to-read way to write code, and probably ought to be available on "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"every type"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":":"}]},{"code":["func transform<Transformed, Error>(","  _ transform: (Self) throws(Error) -> Transformed",") throws(Error) -> Transformed {","  try transform(self)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"But that’s not specific to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":", and is not included in this package."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"We "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"could"}]},{"type":"text","text":" restrict the transformation to require mapping similar types of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":"s, such as"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"Result<Int, Never>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ➡️ ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result<String, any Error>","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"That would look like this:","type":"text"}]},{"code":["func transform<NewSuccess, NewFailure, Error>(","  _ transform: (Self) throws(Error) -> Result<NewSuccess, NewFailure>",") throws(Error) -> Result<NewSuccess, NewFailure> {","  try transform(self)","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Even with this new restriction, the possibilities are so vast in what can be accomplished there, that it’s not worth creating a function for. And so again, this "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"type":"text","text":" is not included in this package either."}]},{"level":3,"text":"flatMap","type":"heading","anchor":"flatMap"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"type":"text","text":" is the closest to a general-purpose "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"type":"text","text":" method that this package works with. The capabilities are different in only two respects:"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"type":"text","text":"‘s’ "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"type":"text","text":" closure operates only on a wrapped value, instead of an entire "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" cannot modify the wrapped error type."}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The “"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flat"},{"type":"text","text":"” in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"type":"text","text":" refers to the way that it introduces no more “nesting” than the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":" represented before transformation. For example,"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Result<String, Never>.flatMap"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":", when supplied with a ","type":"text"},{"code":"transform","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" closure returning type","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Result<Int, Never>"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":", will return","type":"text"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Result<Int, Never>"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":", as opposed to an “unflattened”"}]},{"syntax":"swift","code":["Result<Result<Int, Never>, Never>"],"type":"codeListing"},{"type":"thematicBreak"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"overridingTitle":"As documented below","type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result\/flatMap(_:)","isActive":true,"overridingTitleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"As documented below"}]},{"type":"text","text":", "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"type":"text","text":" will not throw an error when the transformed "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":" is a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"failure"},{"type":"text","text":", but it will throw an error if the transformation throws an error."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/result\/flatMap(_:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"text":" nearly gets ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" right, but it does not incorporate throwing an error. This version should be deprecated.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"text":"flatMapAndMergeError","type":"heading","anchor":"flatMapAndMergeError"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This is a special case of ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". If ","type":"text"},{"code":"transform","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" throws the untransformed ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type, the error can be forwarded into the transformed ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type, rather than being thrown from ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Both forms are useful. Naming this differently than ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is necessary because it would not be enough, for the compiler, to just add ","type":"text"},{"code":"try","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" in front of another ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" overload.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"text":"map","type":"heading","anchor":"map"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The only difference between "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":" is that map’s "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"transform"},{"type":"text","text":" closure returns a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Success"},{"type":"text","text":", not a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Result"},{"type":"text","text":". Thusly, no “flattening” is necessary."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"As with ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"flatMap"},{"text":", ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/result\/map(_:)"},{"text":" nearly gets ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"text":" right, but it does not incorporate throwing an error. This version should be deprecated.","type":"text"}]},{"level":3,"text":"mapAndMergeError","type":"heading","anchor":"mapAndMergeError"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is to ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMapAndMergeError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is to ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"text":"flatMapFailure","anchor":"flatMapFailure","level":4,"type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is the same idea as ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", except, with a transformation of the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"’s ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type, rather than its ","type":"text"},{"code":"Success","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"As we’ve seen above with ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"map"},{"type":"text","text":", the standard library nearly gets this right, under the problematic* name "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/swift\/result\/flatMapError(_:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":", but it does not incorporate throwing an error. It "},{"type":"emphasis","inlineContent":[{"text":"should","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":", for completeness, but does anyone need that? 🤔 (It won’t be included in this package until we hear that they do.)"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"* It’s problematic because the failure type, while restricted to be an error, is called "},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", not "},{"code":"Error","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". And it’s not clear whether you’re mapping a failure enumeration case, or an error occurring from the transformation closure."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"anchor":"mapFailure","type":"heading","text":"mapFailure"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This is to ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMapFailure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" as ","type":"text"},{"code":"map","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is to ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMap","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"anchor":"mapFailureToSuccess","type":"heading","text":"mapFailureToSuccess"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"This idea only works when the ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" type is going to be “removed”, which is represented by ","type":"text"},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":". So, there’s no point in offering a ","type":"text"},{"code":"flatMapFailureToSuccess","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", as ","type":"text"},{"code":"Result.failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"s can’t be created with if their ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"code":"Never","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"anchor":"mapFailureToSuccessAndErrorToFailure","type":"heading","text":"mapFailureToSuccessAndErrorToFailure"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"This is a niche type of error mapping operation."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"It’s similar to the two “"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"…AndMergeError"},{"type":"text","text":"” methods in that an error thrown from transforming will become a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"failure"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"But it’s dissimilar in that while the error thrown ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"can"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" be ","type":"text"},{"code":"Failure","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", there’s no requirement of that (and it’s likely to be a rare case). So, calling this ","type":"text"},{"code":"mapFailureToSuccessAndMergeError","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" would not generally be accurate.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"kind":"content"}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/hmresult\/mapping-methods"]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult","doc:\/\/HMResult\/documentation\/HMResult\/Swift\/Result"]]},"metadata":{"rol